{
  "_comment": "webhint config for the Microsoft Edge Tools panel. This is a React + Vite + Tailwind SPA; webhint lints .tsx as if it were static HTML, so a few hints fire false positives that are NOT real defects. Source-level a11y is enforced by eslint-plugin-jsx-a11y (JSX-aware, 0 problems) and runtime a11y was verified against the rendered app. We keep the hints that catch genuine issues (axe/keyboard caught a real nested-interactive control; compat-api flags real cross-browser gaps) and disable only the ones that cannot reason about JSX/dynamic values.",
  "hints": {
    "no-inline-styles": "off",
    "axe/aria": "off",
    "axe/forms": "off",
    "axe/structure": "off"
  }
}
